WWW:
http://home.pages.de/~Ruppert/


Changes to last release :

HyperText-DataType-System 40.3 (8.9.96) :

- hypertext.datatype :
  - added WBStart support. See  attribute.
  - added ShowLink option, See also Configuration.
  - added Clipboard support.
  - now the DTA_TextAttr attribute is specified by every link. Thus any other document
    is shown in the same font.
- hyperguide.datatype :
  - added @copyright command
  - added \ and \ attributes. See Link attributes.
  - added TabCycle support. See Configuration.
  - now \@wordwrap is functional
  - many guides uses \ instead of \. Now this works also.
- directory.datatype :
  - Rework. Now it have many features. See Documentation



@endnode
@node "16-color MWB"

 1. First change in your ScreenMode prefs to 16 colors.

 2. Then click on the "16-colors.palette"
    This will just change your first 8 colors (C= are lazy fucks who should
    be dead dead dead... So much for "MULTICOLOR")

   Now your WB will look like shit (true Commodore style) ;-)
 3 .Change your MagicWB deamon to
    Run >NIL: C:MagicWB-Demon 4,123,123,123 5,175,175,175 6,170,144,124 7,255,169,151 8,0,0,255 9,50,50,50 10,96,128,96 11,226,209,119 12,255,212,203 13,122,96,72 14,210,210,210 15,229,93,93

 You might have two deamons, one i User-startup and one in Startup-sequence.
 I dont know why this is so, make sure you change BOTH.
 Now reset and all should be fine :-)

 And also if you want to remove that so called "feature" myself considers to be a BUG,
 hat makes the MWB-logo appear randomly after reset, then delete/rename s:mti.data

@endnode